article.headline: Kornet blocks Wagner's last-second layup as Spurs hold off Magic, 114-112
article.description: Luke Kornet blocked Franz Wagner's last-second layup, DeAaron Fox scored 31 points and the San Antonio Spurs beat the Orlando Magic 114-112 on Wednesday night.
article.linkText: Kornet blocks Wagner's last-second layup as Spurs hold off Magic, 114-112

images.caption: San Antonio Spurs vs. Orlando Magic: Game Highlights

video.headline: San Antonio Spurs vs. Orlando Magic: Game Highlights
video.caption: San Antonio Spurs vs. Orlando Magic: Game Highlights
video.title: San Antonio Spurs vs. Orlando Magic: Game Highlights
video.description: San Antonio Spurs vs. Orlando Magic: Game Highlights

tracking.trackingName: NBA_One-Play (San Antonio Spurs vs. Orlando Magic: Game Highlights) 2025/12/04 ESHEET

article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. -- Luke Kornet blocked Franz Wagner's last-second layup, DeAaron Fox scored 31 points and the San Antonio Spurs beat the Orlando Magic 114-112 on Wednesday night. Fox scored the Spurs' final 10 points, the last on two free throws with 1.4 seconds left after a foul on Orlando's Jonathan Isaac. Orlando got the ball to Wagner under the basket, but Kornet swatted it out of bounds as the horn sounded, his third block of the game. San Antonio has won seven of nine with Victor Wembanyama out with a strained left calf. Wagner led Orlando with 25 points. Jalen Suggs added 24 points and three steals before fouling out with 25.6 seconds left. Desmond Bane, coming off consecutive 37-point games, finished with 14 points and six assists after hitting two big shots down the stretch. It was the Magic's third loss in 10 games since they lost Paolo Bancherro to a strained groin. Dylan Harper came off the San Antonio bench with 16 points, five rebounds and five assists, and Devin Vassell had 15 points and six rebounds. Fox had seven of the Spurs' 19 turnovers. Up next Spurs: At Cleveland on Friday night. Magic: Host Miami on Friday night. ------ AP NBA: https://apnews.com/hub/nba
